What is Polymyxin B Sulfate API?
Polymyxin B Sulfate Active Pharmaceutical Ingredient (API) is a polypeptide antibiotic used as the essential active substance in pharmaceutical formulations designed to treat severe multidrug-resistant Gram-negative bacterial infections. It is considered a last-resort antibiotic for combating pathogens such as Klebsiella pneumoniae, Pseudomonas aeruginosa, and Acinetobacter baumannii, particularly when resistance to carbapenems and other antibiotics develops.

Modern Polymyxin B Sulfate API manufacturing involves advanced fermentation and purification technologies while maintaining stringent pharmaceutical quality standards.

Key characteristics include:

·         High-purity pharmaceutical-grade API for injectable formulations

·         Fermentation-based production with strict GMP compliance

·         Effective against carbapenem-resistant Gram-negative bacteria

·         Critical component in hospital critical-care antibiotic therapies

·         Suitable for combination antibiotic formulations

·         Stringent quality control to minimize impurity-related toxicity

By providing reliable treatment against life-threatening resistant infections, Polymyxin B Sulfate API remains an indispensable component of modern antimicrobial therapy despite increasing regulatory oversight.

