Key Market Drivers
1. Rising Prevalence of Multidrug-Resistant Infections
The growing incidence of antimicrobial resistance worldwide is significantly increasing demand for Polymyxin B Sulfate API. With over 1.27 million deaths annually attributed to antibiotic resistance, healthcare providers increasingly rely on polymyxin-based therapies as one of the final treatment options against carbapenem-resistant Gram-negative infections.

The World Health Organization continues to classify polymyxins among the most critically important antimicrobials, supporting sustained market demand.

2. Expanding Healthcare Infrastructure in Emerging Economies
Rapid healthcare development across Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and other emerging markets is driving higher demand for injectable antibiotics used in intensive care units.

Growing investments in hospitals, pharmaceutical manufacturing, and antimicrobial stewardship programs are increasing consumption of pharmaceutical-grade Polymyxin B Sulfate API, particularly in countries experiencing high rates of hospital-acquired infections.

3. Advances in Combination Antibiotic Therapies
Clinical research increasingly supports combining Polymyxin B with carbapenems and other β-lactam antibiotics to improve treatment outcomes against multidrug-resistant pathogens.

Pharmaceutical manufacturers are developing advanced combination formulations requiring highly purified API, creating additional growth opportunities for premium-grade manufacturers.

